EX PARTE APPLICATION FOR ORDER SHORTENING TIME ON PLAINTIFF'S MOTION TO COMPEL DEFENDANT'S DEPOSITION; REQUEST FOR MONETARY SANCTIONS; REQUEST FOR LIMITED LEAVE AFTER DISCOVERY CUTOFF; AND FOR CONDENSED BRIEFING SCHEDULE; SUPPORTING DECLARATION AND PROPOSED ORDER
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Ex Parte Hearing:**
Date: **Thursday, November 13, 2025**
Time: **9:00 a.m.**
Dept: **R12**

**Trial Date:** **July 13, 2026**
**Discovery Cutoff:** **October 22, 2025**

To the Court, the Clerk of the Court, and to Defendant **Megan Nicole Bentley** and her counsel of record:

Plaintiff **Michael James Romero** ("Plaintiff") hereby applies ex parte for an **Order Shortening Time** on **Plaintiff's Motion to Compel Defendant's Deposition; Request for Monetary Sanctions; and Request for Limited Leave After Discovery Cutoff** (the "Motion"), and for a **condensed briefing schedule** on that Motion.

The ex parte relief sought is **strictly limited to scheduling**. Plaintiff does **not** ask the Court to decide the merits of the Motion, or to award any sanctions or other substantive relief, at the ex parte hearing. The merits of the Motion --- including Plaintiff's requests under **CCP § 2025.450** and **CCP § 2024.050** --- will be heard and decided at the advanced hearing on the Motion.

**Relief Requested (CRC 3.1201(1), 3.1300(b); CCP § 1005(b)).**
Plaintiff moves ex parte for an order:

1.  Shortening time and advancing the hearing on the Motion from its current setting of **February 11, 2026 at 9:00 a.m. in Dept. R12** to the **earliest date convenient for the Court**;

2.  Setting a condensed briefing schedule on the Motion, with Opposition and Reply deadlines measured in court days before the advanced hearing date; and

3.  Confirming that the merits of the Motion (including the requests for monetary sanctions and for limited leave after the discovery cutoff) will be heard and decided **only at the advanced hearing on the regularly noticed Motion**, not at this ex parte appearance.

This Application is made pursuant to **CRC 3.1200--3.1207** (ex parte rules), **CRC 3.1300(b)** (order shortening time), and **CCP § 1005(b)** (notice period and court's power to shorten time), on the grounds that: (a) Defendant failed to appear for her properly noticed deposition without obtaining a protective order; (b) the **general discovery cutoff has now passed** while Defendant's deposition remains outstanding; (c) the case has a firm **trial date of July 13, 2026**; and (d) the Court's ordinary law and motion calendar currently sets the Motion on **February 11, 2026**, which will effectively deprive Plaintiff of a fair opportunity to obtain and use Defendant's deposition testimony in discovery, expert preparation, motion practice, and trial.

Good cause is shown in the concurrently filed **Declaration of Michael James Romero (in Support of Ex Parte Application for Order Shortening Time)** and **Declaration of Michael James Romero Regarding Ex Parte Notice**, which are expressly incorporated here by reference.

