PROCEDURAL POSTURE
------------------

-   **Underlying Motion Filed and Pending.**
    Plaintiff's **Motion to Compel Defendant's Deposition; Request for Monetary Sanctions; and Request for Limited Leave After Discovery Cutoff** has been filed and is presently set for hearing on **February 11, 2026 at 9:00 a.m. in Dept. R12**. The Motion seeks an order compelling Defendant's deposition, monetary sanctions under **CCP § 2025.450**, and limited leave under **CCP § 2024.050** to complete Defendant's deposition after the discovery cutoff.

-   **Discovery Cutoff and Trial Setting.**
    The **general discovery cutoff elapsed on October 22, 2025**, and the case is set for a firm **jury trial on July 13, 2026**. Absent timely completion of Defendant's deposition, Plaintiff cannot fairly prepare for expert discovery, pretrial motions, or trial.

-   **Notice of Ex Parte Application (CRC 3.1203--3.1204).**
    On **November 10, 2025**, at approximately **2:35 p.m. Pacific Time**, Plaintiff provided ex parte notice of this Application **by email** to Defendant's counsel, **Randal P. Hannah, Esq.**, at **rhannah@rphannahlaw.com** - advising counsel that Plaintiff would appear ex parte on **November 13, 2025 at 9:00 a.m. in Department R12** at the courthouse located at **8303 Haven Avenue, Rancho Cucamonga, CA 91730**, to seek an **Order Shortening Time on Plaintiff's Motion to Compel Defendant's Deposition; Request for Monetary Sanctions; and Request for Limited Leave After Discovery Cutoff**, and briefly describing the grounds and relief requested. As of **8:00 p.m. on November 12, 2025**, Plaintiff had **not received any response** from Defendant's counsel and therefore does **not know** whether Defendant intends to oppose this ex parte Application. These facts are set forth in more detail in Plaintiff's **Declaration Regarding Ex Parte Notice**.

    Plaintiff will **e-file** the ex parte papers and **serve them on Defendant's counsel** in accordance with the Rules of Court and any applicable local rules. Plaintiff understands that the Court does not issue reservation numbers for ex parte calendars; none has been issued.

